1
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:59,166
When people finish their day
and hurry home,

2
00:00:59,875 --> 00:01:01,416
my day starts.

3
00:01:19,039 --> 00:01:23,080
My diner is open from midnight
to 7:00 in the morning.

4
00:01:23,843 --> 00:01:27,176
They call it "Midnight Diner."

5
00:01:32,641 --> 00:01:34,320
Do I even have customers?

6
00:01:34,636 --> 00:01:36,511
More than you would expect.

7
00:01:38,978 --> 00:01:40,940
MIDNIGHT DINER: TOKYO STORIES

8
00:01:40,940 --> 00:01:46,523
KITSUNE UDON

9
00:01:49,415 --> 00:01:52,915
Is this the right street?
Or it could be wrong?

10
00:01:54,026 --> 00:01:56,609
-Maybe this is the right one.
-It's the one, right?

11
00:01:58,035 --> 00:01:59,118
Sorry.

12
00:02:02,877 --> 00:02:04,127
Okay, this one...

13
00:02:15,575 --> 00:02:16,492
Is this the one?

14
00:02:19,769 --> 00:02:20,934
Look.

15
00:02:22,373 --> 00:02:23,623
Yes, this is the one.

16
00:02:31,521 --> 00:02:33,509
But there are only old people here.

17
00:02:35,738 --> 00:02:37,644
Haruna, you go in first.

18
00:02:37,644 --> 00:02:39,951
You wanted to come here, Akina.

19
00:02:39,951 --> 00:02:41,933
That's true, but it doesn't matter.

20
00:02:41,933 --> 00:02:43,248
You go first.

21
00:02:43,248 --> 00:02:44,357
No, I can't.

22
00:02:44,357 --> 00:02:45,464
Hey, you two!

23
00:02:47,208 --> 00:02:48,291
Can I go in?

24
00:02:51,118 --> 00:02:52,285
Please!

25
00:02:54,178 --> 00:02:55,594
Good evening.

26
00:02:55,983 --> 00:02:57,233
Welcome.

27
00:02:59,620 --> 00:03:03,393
It's unusual for Marilyn
to bring young girls here.

28
00:03:03,393 --> 00:03:04,459
Are they new dancers?

29
00:03:04,459 --> 00:03:05,773
No, they aren't.

30
00:03:05,773 --> 00:03:06,940
They were outside.

31
00:03:07,683 --> 00:03:10,169
Master, my usual and shochu on the rocks.

32
00:03:10,169 --> 00:03:11,003
Sure.

33
00:03:11,804 --> 00:03:13,054
How about you two?

34
00:03:16,574 --> 00:03:18,658
Can you make kitsune udon?

35
00:03:20,291 --> 00:03:21,847
Yes, I can.

36
00:03:22,282 --> 00:03:24,074
Two, please.

37
00:03:24,703 --> 00:03:25,578
Sure.

38
00:03:56,249 --> 00:03:56,977
Here you go.

39
00:04:07,666 --> 00:04:10,124
Please get me a role in the next audition.

40
00:04:10,963 --> 00:04:12,595
Even a small role.

41
00:04:12,942 --> 00:04:14,109
Please.

42
00:04:17,303 --> 00:04:19,619
What do you two do for a living?

43
00:04:20,318 --> 00:04:23,276
We are trying to be
voice actors for animations.

44
00:04:23,927 --> 00:04:28,566
We have an audition tomorrow.
We're making a wish on kitsune udon.

45
00:04:29,034 --> 00:04:29,841
Right?

46
00:04:29,841 --> 00:04:30,424
Yeah.

47
00:04:31,245 --> 00:04:32,387
Making a wish?

48
00:04:33,982 --> 00:04:37,066
I heard his kitsune udon would
bring you good luck, correct?

49
00:04:37,976 --> 00:04:39,850
I've never heard of it before.

50
00:04:40,256 --> 00:04:43,863
A friend who had this dish
had a successful audition.

51
00:04:43,863 --> 00:04:45,297
I saw it on Instagram.

52
00:04:45,297 --> 00:04:47,257
It's by luck.

53
00:04:47,257 --> 00:04:49,830
It's just an ordinary kitsune udon.

54
00:04:51,950 --> 00:04:53,534
Is that so?

55
00:04:53,868 --> 00:04:55,967
But they could be right.

56
00:04:56,274 --> 00:05:00,211
Because he offers a deep-fried tofu
to the shrine every day.

57
00:05:00,417 --> 00:05:02,131
That's right.

58
00:05:03,262 --> 00:05:04,796
Never say never.

59
00:05:12,951 --> 00:05:14,368
-Let's eat.
-Let's eat.

60
00:05:28,221 --> 00:05:29,346
Delicious.

61
00:05:31,597 --> 00:05:32,972
It's so good, isn't it?

62
00:05:35,671 --> 00:05:36,504
Hey.

63
00:05:37,070 --> 00:05:40,237
You could notice my dialect,
on that last line, couldn't you?

64
00:05:41,224 --> 00:05:44,141
You'll be fine
if you are careful about intonation.

65
00:05:46,941 --> 00:05:49,441
"That night, on the bridge..."

66
00:05:50,902 --> 00:05:51,999
"On the bridge..."

67
00:05:52,358 --> 00:05:53,457
"On the bridge..."

68
00:05:53,819 --> 00:05:54,846
"On the bridge."

69
00:05:55,225 --> 00:05:56,809
I'm not so sure any more.

70
00:05:56,809 --> 00:05:58,829
No worries. You're okay.

71
00:05:58,829 --> 00:06:00,429
-Really?
-Say it again.

72
00:06:02,108 --> 00:06:05,330
"On that night, on the bridge,
I saw a man running--"

73
00:06:05,322 --> 00:06:06,457
"On the bridge."

74
00:06:06,905 --> 00:06:07,698
"On the bridge."

75
00:06:07,853 --> 00:06:09,045
"On the bridge."

76
00:06:10,756 --> 00:06:12,798
-"On the bridge."
-That's it.

77
00:06:15,934 --> 00:06:17,610
You sound good!

78
00:06:18,004 --> 00:06:20,496
I'll treat you both tonight
'cause I'm a good person.

79
00:06:20,966 --> 00:06:21,975
Really?

80
00:06:22,367 --> 00:06:24,735
There's no such thing as a free lunch.

81
00:06:26,941 --> 00:06:29,615
I think you should just thank her.

82
00:06:41,990 --> 00:06:43,689
We both didn't make it.

83
00:06:44,775 --> 00:06:46,031
I see...

84
00:06:46,589 --> 00:06:48,214
It didn't bring you good luck.

85
00:06:49,023 --> 00:06:53,031
They say voice-acting jobs
are very hard to get.

86
00:06:53,694 --> 00:06:56,985
But Haruna was
one of four final candidates.

87
00:06:57,891 --> 00:07:02,924
An entertainment management company
talked to Akina personally, though.

88
00:07:03,287 --> 00:07:04,412
That's great!

89
00:07:04,616 --> 00:07:08,004
You both have moved forward
toward your dream a little.

90
00:07:08,263 --> 00:07:09,972
It did bring you luck.

91
00:07:10,755 --> 00:07:11,448
Here you go.

92
00:07:15,602 --> 00:07:17,342
Two deep-fried tofu today?

93
00:07:18,357 --> 00:07:21,389
A special treat from me.

94
00:07:21,893 --> 00:07:23,018
Great!

95
00:07:23,856 --> 00:07:26,981
Let's make sure we bring him
better news next time.

96
00:07:29,406 --> 00:07:32,652
-So nice to be young. I'm so jealous.
-Let's eat.

97
00:07:33,027 --> 00:07:36,105
Don't be silly.
You're still young, Marilyn.

98
00:07:36,902 --> 00:07:37,860
Don't bother.

99
00:07:42,400 --> 00:07:45,650
About six months later...

100
00:07:48,257 --> 00:07:49,257
Good evening.

101
00:07:51,178 --> 00:07:52,178
Welcome.

102
00:07:52,710 --> 00:07:53,835
Long time no see.

103
00:07:57,931 --> 00:07:59,514
Could I have kitsune udon?

104
00:08:00,521 --> 00:08:01,387
Sure.

105
00:08:08,924 --> 00:08:13,187
I heard you've got a job as a voice actor.

106
00:08:13,966 --> 00:08:16,569
Haruna told me the other day.

107
00:08:17,125 --> 00:08:17,959
Yes.

108
00:08:18,804 --> 00:08:23,574
Not exactly as a voice actor, though.
I joined an idol group of voice actors.

109
00:08:24,910 --> 00:08:28,701
So gigs and fan conventions only.

110
00:08:29,409 --> 00:08:31,201
It's not my ideal job.

111
00:08:31,826 --> 00:08:34,611
But it could lead to something else.

112
00:08:36,098 --> 00:08:37,137
That's the spirit!

113
00:08:39,633 --> 00:08:42,494
Has Haruna been here lately?

114
00:08:43,174 --> 00:08:46,507
Yeah, sometimes after her part-time job.

115
00:08:48,667 --> 00:08:49,602
You haven't seen her?

116
00:08:50,583 --> 00:08:51,666
Not much.

117
00:08:52,604 --> 00:08:55,325
It seems she's having
a difficult time auditioning.

118
00:08:56,861 --> 00:08:58,604
Why don't you give her a call?

119
00:09:01,681 --> 00:09:03,140
Not now.

120
00:09:04,047 --> 00:09:09,257
Because the more I try to cheer her up,
the worse she'd feel.

121
00:09:23,609 --> 00:09:24,941
We're really sorry.

122
00:09:26,295 --> 00:09:27,212
Yes.

123
00:09:28,793 --> 00:09:32,812
Yes. We will be more careful.

124
00:09:33,438 --> 00:09:34,397
Yes.

125
00:09:35,322 --> 00:09:37,031
We are terribly sorry.

126
00:09:37,368 --> 00:09:38,289
Yes.

127
00:10:14,051 --> 00:10:15,426
Kitsune udon?

128
00:10:16,711 --> 00:10:17,753
No.

129
00:10:18,923 --> 00:10:21,148
No point in me making a wish.

130
00:10:22,140 --> 00:10:23,515
What's wrong?

131
00:10:27,704 --> 00:10:28,538
Welcome.

132
00:10:29,028 --> 00:10:30,278
Warm sake, please.

133
00:10:31,607 --> 00:10:33,300
-Are you okay?
-Yes.

134
00:10:33,589 --> 00:10:35,339
I'll go home right after one drink.

135
00:10:36,100 --> 00:10:38,616
He is Mr. Nobuta.

136
00:10:39,058 --> 00:10:43,571
He is a manga artist
who became very popular a few years ago.

137
00:10:44,475 --> 00:10:47,883
He hasn't been doing well
recently, though.

138
00:10:50,381 --> 00:10:52,464
Here you go.

139
00:10:56,051 --> 00:10:58,321
Money doesn't make you happy.

140
00:10:58,830 --> 00:10:59,830
Again?

141
00:11:00,860 --> 00:11:04,165
I can't get back the money I spent
on the woman, or her love, either.

142
00:11:05,028 --> 00:11:08,109
Master, what have I got now?

143
00:11:08,499 --> 00:11:09,643
Work.

144
00:11:10,028 --> 00:11:11,818
Go home now and do it.

145
00:11:12,351 --> 00:11:13,851
That's harsh.

146
00:11:20,679 --> 00:11:21,494
What?

147
00:11:23,697 --> 00:11:26,697
You're Mr. Yukio Nobuta, aren't you?

148
00:11:28,319 --> 00:11:29,818
I'm a huge fan of yours.

149
00:11:30,364 --> 00:11:33,464
-Ah, is that so?
-Yes.

150
00:11:33,464 --> 00:11:35,819
-Women always say that.
-What?

151
00:11:35,819 --> 00:11:38,528
But usually,
they just happen to know my name.

152
00:11:38,861 --> 00:11:40,558
Are you a student?

153
00:11:41,293 --> 00:11:44,646
No. I don't think you'll believe me,

154
00:11:45,081 --> 00:11:48,322
but I watched your animation on TV
when I was a high school student.

155
00:11:49,241 --> 00:11:51,898
I'm trying to be a voice actor.

156
00:11:51,898 --> 00:11:53,585
You're so typical.

157
00:11:54,791 --> 00:11:57,659
People think that they understand
everything by just reading some.

158
00:11:58,016 --> 00:12:00,670
If you understand that much,
you should write!

159
00:12:02,832 --> 00:12:03,866
Mr. Nobuta.

160
00:12:04,392 --> 00:12:05,625
Cut it out.

161
00:12:06,125 --> 00:12:06,803
But...

162
00:12:07,829 --> 00:12:08,949
It's true.

163
00:12:09,276 --> 00:12:11,946
UNTIL IT BECOMES LIGHT
YUKIO NOBUTA

164
00:12:14,937 --> 00:12:15,943
Why do you have this?

165
00:12:18,331 --> 00:12:21,247
It was 30,000 yen on an online auction.

166
00:12:22,058 --> 00:12:24,481
I saved money and finally got it.

167
00:12:25,100 --> 00:12:27,084
I've read all your books.

168
00:12:28,183 --> 00:12:29,725
Until It Becomes Light.

169
00:12:33,913 --> 00:12:36,332
I heard you can't find it,
even in the secondhand bookstores.

170
00:12:37,684 --> 00:12:39,101
This is my very first book.

171
00:12:40,298 --> 00:12:43,881
It didn't sell well,
and later it was out of print.

172
00:12:45,823 --> 00:12:46,823
I see.

173
00:12:49,167 --> 00:12:51,757
I watch God's Miso Soup on TV every week.

174
00:12:52,119 --> 00:12:54,244
I also read the one in
STEP magazine every week.

175
00:12:55,391 --> 00:12:57,756
Well, I haven't published
any episodes in it lately.

176
00:12:59,019 --> 00:13:03,144
Publisher says animation
will take over comic books.

177
00:13:06,710 --> 00:13:08,835
How come you don't write?

178
00:13:12,399 --> 00:13:13,441
Because I can't.

179
00:13:15,766 --> 00:13:17,432
They'll probably cut me off soon.

180
00:13:18,693 --> 00:13:21,526
But I guess it's better
than writing bad ones.

181
00:13:24,611 --> 00:13:28,278
You can't tell if it's bad
until you actually write.

182
00:13:30,651 --> 00:13:34,734
I always fail auditions...

183
00:13:35,864 --> 00:13:38,322
and I wonder if I'm really suited
for voice acting.

184
00:13:39,053 --> 00:13:41,136
But you never know until you do it!

185
00:13:44,544 --> 00:13:45,744
I'm sorry.

186
00:13:46,239 --> 00:13:47,489
Don't be.

187
00:13:48,527 --> 00:13:49,902
You're right.

188
00:13:51,408 --> 00:13:54,825
But the truth hurts me at the moment.

189
00:13:56,617 --> 00:13:58,417
I'm terribly sorry.

190
00:13:58,417 --> 00:14:01,125
We can't compare my problems with yours...

191
00:14:01,237 --> 00:14:03,685
Master, this is for both of us.

192
00:14:03,685 --> 00:14:06,005
Give me the change next time.

193
00:14:06,593 --> 00:14:07,582
Sure.

194
00:14:17,564 --> 00:14:19,814
Setting is now complete.

195
00:14:19,814 --> 00:14:21,606
Do you have any more concerns?

196
00:14:22,942 --> 00:14:23,659
Yes.

197
00:14:24,543 --> 00:14:26,130
Yes. Thank you very much.

198
00:14:44,253 --> 00:14:45,586
We'll play the message.

199
00:14:46,552 --> 00:14:47,844
Hello, Haruna?

200
00:14:48,766 --> 00:14:52,419
I wonder how you're doing.
I haven't seen you at auditions lately--

201
00:15:10,011 --> 00:15:12,427
How's your work these days?

202
00:15:15,049 --> 00:15:16,549
I think I'll quit.

203
00:15:18,324 --> 00:15:19,654
My production company told me...

204
00:15:20,179 --> 00:15:22,804
they'd end the contract
if I can't do well.

205
00:15:24,773 --> 00:15:25,981
I understand now.

206
00:15:27,345 --> 00:15:30,387
I'm happy enough just watching animations.

207
00:15:31,472 --> 00:15:34,639
I don't want to end up hating it,
trying to get a job in the industry.

208
00:15:37,411 --> 00:15:39,944
GOD'S MISO SOUP STARTS AGAIN
Have you read this?

209
00:15:40,662 --> 00:15:42,854
Yes, of course.

210
00:15:43,413 --> 00:15:46,288
Mr. Nobuta said the other day,

211
00:15:47,538 --> 00:15:49,391
"I could make it, thanks to Haruna.

212
00:15:53,337 --> 00:15:57,748
I learned from her that you'll never know
until you do something."

213
00:16:00,357 --> 00:16:03,679
I got this from him.

214
00:16:04,469 --> 00:16:06,639
He asked me to give it you.

215
00:16:13,028 --> 00:16:16,361
GOD'S MISO SOUP
VOICE ACTOR AUDITION FOR A NEW CHARACTER

216
00:16:31,001 --> 00:16:32,302
Yes. Thank you.

217
00:16:32,302 --> 00:16:34,177
Thank you.

218
00:16:39,321 --> 00:16:42,628
You've got a gig and a fan convention
right after this audition.

219
00:16:42,628 --> 00:16:43,355
Yes.

220
00:16:43,355 --> 00:16:46,679
I'll be there after I finish
another appointment.

221
00:16:46,679 --> 00:16:47,739
Thank you.

222
00:16:47,739 --> 00:16:48,886
-Don't be late.
-Of course not.

223
00:16:56,223 --> 00:16:57,973
-Please have a seat.
-Yes.

224
00:17:20,149 --> 00:17:22,215
-Excuse me...
-Sorry.

225
00:17:24,634 --> 00:17:25,717
Long time no see.

226
00:17:42,972 --> 00:17:45,839
SHOTA
I'm sorry...

227
00:17:45,839 --> 00:17:48,619
SHOTA
...but I couldn't do it.

228
00:17:50,311 --> 00:17:54,223
In this world, some can make it,
and some cannot.

229
00:17:55,861 --> 00:17:57,652
I'm the one who cannot.

230
00:17:59,041 --> 00:18:00,952
"Don't decide if you can't do it!

231
00:18:02,384 --> 00:18:03,975
You do know...

232
00:18:04,642 --> 00:18:05,495
SHINO

233
00:18:05,495 --> 00:18:07,642
You just don't want to fail."
SHINO

234
00:18:07,642 --> 00:18:09,429
SHINO

235
00:18:09,429 --> 00:18:10,229
"But...
SHINO

236
00:18:10,229 --> 00:18:11,135
SHINO

237
00:18:11,745 --> 00:18:15,537
You never know the outcome
until you try doing it."

238
00:18:19,524 --> 00:18:21,345
Thank you very much.

239
00:18:21,769 --> 00:18:23,061
Thank you very much.

240
00:18:25,204 --> 00:18:26,454
She was good.

241
00:18:27,549 --> 00:18:30,008
Next, Ms. Haruna Honma.

242
00:18:30,689 --> 00:18:31,522
Yes.

243
00:18:44,583 --> 00:18:46,666
I'm the one who cannot.

244
00:18:48,133 --> 00:18:49,883
"Don't decide if you can't do it.

245
00:18:51,079 --> 00:18:52,871
You do know...

246
00:18:53,988 --> 00:18:56,238
You just don't want to fail.

247
00:18:57,742 --> 00:18:58,825
But...

248
00:18:59,618 --> 00:19:03,701
you never know the outcome
until you try doing it."

249
00:19:24,616 --> 00:19:26,116
Thank you very much.

250
00:19:27,787 --> 00:19:29,120
Wait. One more time.

251
00:19:31,187 --> 00:19:35,247
Please start again from page two.
Tone down a little this time.

252
00:19:35,247 --> 00:19:36,080
Can you do it?

253
00:19:37,689 --> 00:19:39,884
Yes. I'll try.

254
00:19:40,377 --> 00:19:42,877
-Please start from the beginning.
-Yes.

255
00:19:48,816 --> 00:19:50,358
Thank you so much.

256
00:19:50,991 --> 00:19:52,366
I have high hopes for you.

257
00:19:52,366 --> 00:19:53,366
I'll try my best.

258
00:19:54,355 --> 00:19:55,915
Thank you so much!

259
00:19:55,915 --> 00:19:57,069
Keep up the good work.

260
00:19:57,069 --> 00:19:58,361
Sure.

261
00:20:22,489 --> 00:20:23,989
Congratulations, Haruna.

262
00:20:25,378 --> 00:20:26,503
You were great.

263
00:20:28,283 --> 00:20:29,950
I just wanted to tell you that.

264
00:20:34,200 --> 00:20:35,325
Thanks.

265
00:20:36,950 --> 00:20:38,200
But I was not that good.

266
00:20:39,316 --> 00:20:42,525
I voiced my feelings, not the character's.

267
00:20:42,904 --> 00:20:44,613
You need to express that
as a professional.

268
00:20:46,866 --> 00:20:51,073
But I'm so happy you've got the role.

269
00:20:57,004 --> 00:20:57,808
That's not true.

270
00:20:59,651 --> 00:21:02,355
I'm so gutted!

271
00:21:06,497 --> 00:21:10,696
I'll try much harder to catch up with you.

272
00:21:16,414 --> 00:21:17,306
Sorry.

273
00:21:20,745 --> 00:21:21,657
For what?

274
00:21:25,673 --> 00:21:27,464
I was so jealous of you, Akina.

275
00:21:30,134 --> 00:21:32,134
We've been good friends for so long.

276
00:21:33,629 --> 00:21:36,226
I should have been happy for you instead.

277
00:21:41,882 --> 00:21:46,038
We have our future ahead.

278
00:21:57,629 --> 00:21:58,735
Thank you.

279
00:22:06,130 --> 00:22:08,926
I need to go now.

280
00:22:11,102 --> 00:22:11,816
Okay.

281
00:22:14,224 --> 00:22:15,729
See you. Bye.

282
00:22:16,226 --> 00:22:17,601
Bye.

283
00:22:28,594 --> 00:22:30,636
You just don't want to fail.

284
00:22:31,241 --> 00:22:36,241
But you never know the outcome
until you try doing it.

285
00:22:39,573 --> 00:22:40,297
Yeah.

286
00:22:41,372 --> 00:22:44,705
On Koro Koro Sendari Matogi Sowaka.

287
00:22:55,108 --> 00:22:57,283
Great work!

288
00:22:57,283 --> 00:23:00,217
I don't usually watch anime,
but it was great.

289
00:23:00,851 --> 00:23:02,226
Such a small screen, though.

290
00:23:05,299 --> 00:23:06,674
Here you go.

291
00:23:10,024 --> 00:23:11,694
Master's kitsune udon...

292
00:23:12,049 --> 00:23:13,710
It did bring us good luck.

293
00:23:14,102 --> 00:23:15,030
Yeah.

294
00:23:15,440 --> 00:23:17,572
Master, thank you so much for that.

295
00:23:18,483 --> 00:23:19,316
Not me.

296
00:23:20,025 --> 00:23:21,540
You both have tried so hard.

297
00:23:22,872 --> 00:23:25,090
I was the first one
who treated you this dish.

298
00:23:25,450 --> 00:23:28,065
If asked about this in an interview,
do mention me.

299
00:23:28,566 --> 00:23:29,339
-Yes.
-Yes.

300
00:23:29,664 --> 00:23:33,164
See. I told you,
"There's no such thing as a free lunch."

301
00:23:34,491 --> 00:23:37,188
You're so serious. I'm just kidding.

302
00:23:37,548 --> 00:23:39,673
Eat before the noodles get soggy.

303
00:23:41,626 --> 00:23:43,084
-Let's eat!
-Let's eat!

304
00:23:44,256 --> 00:23:45,145
Here you are.

305
00:23:45,451 --> 00:23:46,618
-Thank you so much.
-Thank you so much.

306
00:23:47,514 --> 00:23:48,601
As for a deep-fried tofu,

307
00:23:48,601 --> 00:23:52,214
you can remove excess oil
by pressing firmly with a sheet of paper.

308
00:23:52,214 --> 00:23:54,247
If you cook it with enough seasoning,

309
00:23:54,247 --> 00:23:56,262
the juice goes into the soup,
and it's delicious.

310
00:23:57,553 --> 00:23:58,553
Here you go.

311
00:24:02,516 --> 00:24:04,264
Oh, dear...

312
00:24:04,264 --> 00:24:06,641
Master, don't you have any good ideas?

313
00:24:06,641 --> 00:24:07,916
In another slump again?

314
00:24:07,916 --> 00:24:11,671
Don't say that.
I must suffer to create something great.

315
00:24:11,671 --> 00:24:12,754
Right?

316
00:24:16,554 --> 00:24:17,679
What are you doing?

317
00:24:18,201 --> 00:24:20,993
We're making a wish for your good work.

318
00:24:27,170 --> 00:24:28,670
-Good night!
-Good night!

